HEADWORD: kanchil
<hw>kan"chil</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Malay
<ets>canch⟦imac⟧l</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A small
chevrotain of the genus <gen>Tragulus</gen>, esp. <spn>Tragulus
pygm⟦ae⟧us</spn>, or <spn>Tragulus kanchil</spn>, inhabiting Java,
Sumatra, and adjacent islands; a deerlet. It is noted for its agility
and cunning.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

